Light/Shadow Effects System

The light/shadow effects system provides a more elegant and consistent way to handle 
glowing and shadowy objects in SneezyMUD. It replaces the old approach of using affect 
slots for light effects with a dedicated property in the TObj class.

COMMANDS:

@set light <object> <value>
  Sets a positive light (glow) effect on an object.
  The value must be positive.
  Example: @set light sword 3

@set shadow <object> <value>
  Sets a negative light (shadow) effect on an object.
  The value will be converted to negative if positive.
  Example: @set shadow dagger 2

@clear light <object>
  Clears any light or shadow effect from an object.
  Example: @clear light sword

NOTES:

- Glowing objects (positive light value) are more visible and contribute light to the environment.
- Shadowy objects (negative light value) are less visible and absorb light from the environment.
- Objects cannot have both glow and shadow effects simultaneously. Setting one will remove the other.
- The light effect value is displayed in the @stat output for objects.

